    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b571e562_62d25c4b",
        "filename": "cq/api/bigquery/attempt.proto",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003190
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-06T22:19:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What about when CQ cancels a build (e.g. due to new patchset upload)? That\u0027s technically within control of CQ, triggered by external event...",
      "parentUuid": "9258b3e3_99d0f0a9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "b36976b355f3da35b69101971832023f8e7a91bd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "df4e78b6_45242147",
        "filename": "cq/api/bigquery/attempt.proto",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-06T23:26:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "by this very technical definition, each attempt\u0027s final status is a CQ\u0027s own decision.\n\nFrom perspective of someone writing a query, I think what is truly important is whether failure can be attributed to\n* CQ\u0027s own issue\n* quality of CL and/or flakiness of testing\n* User actions, like uploading new patchset\n\nOur team will optimize for reduction of INFRA_FAILURE.\nBubblesort team will optimize for reduction of false-\"FAILURE\" (ie FAILURE followed by SUCCESS)\n\nAnd ABORTED can probably be mostly ignored, as it\u0027s not something we can directly affect, unless it\u0027s due to Gerrit issues.",
      "parentUuid": "b571e562_62d25c4b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 41
      },
      "revId": "b36976b355f3da35b69101971832023f8e7a91bd",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
